<TITLE> UK local govt minister arrives Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 4 (bdnews24.com)  The UK's secretary of state for communities and local government John Denham MP arrives in Dhaka on Monday. The minister's visit aims to enhance the strong bonds between the societies of Bangladesh and the UK, a statement of the British High Commission said. The visit will also be an opportunity to restate the UK's commitments to assist Bangladesh in the fields of education, climate change and democracy, said the statement. During his three-day visit Denham is due to meet prime minister Sheikh Hasina and ministers for foreign affairs, local government, education and women and childrren's affairs. He will also meet the Sylhet Mayor and community representatives in Sylhet and visit a UK funded poverty eradication programme there. He will participate in a discussion with Bangladeshis on a range of issues too, said the statement.
